An HTTP/1.0 endpoint identical to access_log_json in shape (handler
returns 200 ok), but the log block declares on_error: abort. If the
audit log file becomes unwritable (disk full, FS read-only, target
directory removed), the next failed write terminates the process with
exit status 1 instead of silently dropping the line. This is the
fail-closed posture an Article 12 audit chain needs: no log line
persisted means no claim that the request was processed.
